paragraphs: Sparkling wine is the wine style of celebrations; bubbly, fruity and always delicious. It should always be at hand for that sudden get together with friends or family. Whether it be your first sparkling wine or in search of a new favourite, we have that perfect bottle for you.

campaigns.text2:
Buy Sparkling Wine Near You or Online

Liquorland has been finding customers the best sparkling wine for over twenty years, so you should feel confident in knowing you’ve come to the right place. Not sure what to select? While France has many excellent value sparkling white wines including Moet & Chandon and Mumm Champagnes, closer to home in Australia, there has been an emergence of quality bottles too deriving mostly from King River and Yarra Valley. We stock wonderful wines such as the Coombe and Brown Brothers for you to enjoy. Remember to keep a lookout for specials and daily promotions too.

Choosing your next sparkling has never been more straightforward. You can purchase sparkling wine either online, in person, or through our free click and select service, which will deliver it right to your door. Yes, we can deliver sparkling wine to Melbourne, Sydney, Brisbane and everywhere in between.

Sparkling Wine Serving Suggestions

Sparkling wine is best served chilled and pairs perfectly with fresh seafood molluscs such as oysters, mussels, or clams from the sea. Whether it be a dry sparkling wine or a sweet sparkling wine, both styles are an excellent choice for outdoor or indoor celebrations throughout the year.

Best Food to Pair with Sparkling Wine

  • Seafood
  • Soft Cheeses

FAQs from Sparkling Wine Buyers

Q. What sparkling wine is best?

Moet Chandon and Bollinger to name a few.

Q. Is sparkling wine the same thing as champagne?

Yes, champagne is a sparkling wine, but it can only be called Champagne if it is made within 100 miles of the Champagne area in France's northeastern corner.

Q. Is riesling a sparkling wine?

Yes, a riesling can be a sparkling wine.

Q. How do you drink sparkling wine?

Sparkling wine is often kept in an ice-bucket for 15-20 minutes before serving.
